Inspect an object

Source: R/inspect.R
obj_inspect.Rd

obj_inspect(x) is similar to .Internal(inspect(x)). The main difference is the output is a little more compact, it recurses fully, and avoids getting stuck in infinite loops by using a depth-first search. It also returns a list that you can compute with, and carefully uses colour to highlight the most important details.

obj_inspect(x, expand = character())

Arguments

x

Object to inspect
expand

Optionally, expand components of the true that are usually suppressed. Use:

  • "character" to show underlying entries in the global string pool.

  • "environment" to show the underlying hashtables.

  • "altrep" to show the underlying data.

  • "call" to show the full AST (but ast() is usually superior)

  • "bytecode" to show generated bytecode.

Examples

x <- list(
  TRUE,
  1L,
  runif(100),
  "3"
)
obj_inspect(x)
#> [1:0x7114ea8] <VECSXP[4]> (named:7)
#>   [2:0x3b1a928] <LGLSXP[1]> (named:7)
#>   [3:0x3b1a960] <INTSXP[1]> (named:7)
#>   [4:0x441b5e0] <REALSXP[100]> (named:0)
#>   [5:0x3b1aa08] <STRSXP[1]> (named:7)

# Expand "character" to see underlying CHARSXP entries in the global
# string pool
x <- c("banana", "banana", "apple", "banana")
obj_inspect(x)
#> [1:0x8bb0328] <STRSXP[4]> (named:7)
obj_inspect(x, expand = "character")
#> [1:0x8bb0328] <STRSXP[4]> (named:7)
#>   [2:0x3b1adc0] <CHARSXP> (named:0)
#>   [2:0x3b1adc0]
#>   [3:0x3344500] <CHARSXP> (named:0)
#>   [2:0x3b1adc0]

# Expand altrep to see underlying data
x <- 1:10
obj_inspect(x)
#> [1:0x8c190d8] <INTSXP[10]> (altrep named:7)
obj_inspect(x, expand = "altrep")
#> [1:0x8c190d8] <INTSXP[10]> (altrep named:7)
#>   _class [2:0x228e290] <RAWSXP[144]> (named:0)
#>     _attrib [3:0x22c4e98] <LISTSXP> (named:0)
#>       [4:0x22bd0e8] <SYMSXP: compact_intseq> (named:0)
#>       [5:0x228fa70] <SYMSXP: base> (named:7)
#>       [6:0x22c28b0] <INTSXP[1]> (named:0)
#>   _data1 [7:0x8d52e18] <REALSXP[3]> (named:0)
#>   _data2 <NILSXP>

# Expand environmnets to see the underlying implementation details
e1 <- new.env(hash = FALSE, parent = emptyenv(), size = 3L)
e2 <- new.env(hash = TRUE, parent = emptyenv(), size = 3L)
e1$x <- e2$x <- 1:10

obj_inspect(e1)
#> [1:0x5de71a0] <ENVSXP> (named:7)
#>   x [2:0x60a6788] <INTSXP[10]> (altrep named:7)
#>   _enclos [3:0x2290c98] <ENVSXP: empty> (named:7)
obj_inspect(e1, expand = "environment")
#> [1:0x5de71a0] <ENVSXP> (named:7)
#>   _frame [2:0x60a6e50] <LISTSXP> (named:0)
#>     x [3:0x60a6788] <INTSXP[10]> (altrep named:7)
#>   _hashtab <NILSXP>
#>   _enclos [5:0x2290c98] <ENVSXP: empty> (named:7)
obj_inspect(e2, expand = "environment")
#> [1:0x5f58e70] <ENVSXP> (named:7)
#>   _frame <NILSXP>
#>   _hashtab [3:0x7de0498] <VECSXP[3/1]> (named:0)
#>     [4:0x60a6b40] <LISTSXP> (named:0)
#>       x [5:0x60a6788] <INTSXP[10]> (altrep named:7)
#>     <NILSXP>
#>     <NILSXP>
#>   _enclos [6:0x2290c98] <ENVSXP: empty> (named:7)
